desc:
Use this simple Kanban template to keep the engineering team on the same page and moving through work fluidly.

1. Break down the roadmap by adding tasks as cards to the **Backlog** list.
2. Move the cards one-by-one through **Design** as they becomes more fleshed out. _Pro tip:_ You can enable Power-ups for your favorite design tools like [Figma](https://trello.com/power-ups/59b2e7611e6ece0b35eac16a/figma "‚Äå") or [Invision](https://trello.com/power-ups/596f2cb2d279152540b2bb31 "‚Äå"), in order to easily link and view designs without switching context.
3. When a card is fully specced out and designs are attached, move it to **To Do** for engineers to pick up.
4. Engineers move cards to **Doing** and assign themselves to the cards, so the whole team stays informed of who is working on what.
5. Cards then move through **Code Review** when they're ready for a second set of eyes. The team can set a **List Limit** (with the List Limit Power-up) on the number of cards in Code Review, as a visual indicator for when the team needs to prioritize reviews rather than picking up new work.
6. Once cards move through **Testing** and eventually ship to production, move them to **Done** and celebrate!

listing.description:
#Quickly and easily export your Trello boards and card information to share insights and boost the visibility of your team‚Äôs work. üöÄ

![Board export demo](https://orahapps-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/BE+Directory+Listing+gif+-+April+2021.gif)

##The most comprehensive and customisable export tool for Trello. Export only what you need with the widest range of Trello field options. Eliminate the need to perform time-consuming editing with a variety of popular export formats. 

##Why export from Trello?

- **Quickly extract** your Trello boards and cards for reporting, analysis, back-up, distribution, and transfer to other systems. 
- **Easily share information** with stakeholders who aren‚Äôt on your Trello board.
- **Save time** by only exporting the information you need. 
- **Engage your audience** by exporting boards into the format suitable for your target audience.
- **Fully supported** and reliable Power-Up with dedicated support and development team.  

>"Board Export has cut my admin time by 50% when creating my reports from Trello" 
>- Matheus, Board Export user

##How can it help you?

Export nearly every Trello data point including boards, cards, comments, activity log, checklists, advanced lists, due dates and members. (NB - supported fields vary between export formats. For a full breakdown [click here](https://docs.adaptavist.com/be/latest/data-included-with-exports) )

![Board Exports in Trello your way](https://hub.adaptavist.com/hubfs/Trello/BE%20-%20your%20way.png)


Fully customisable with the ability to pre-select/deselect the exact fields you want to export. 
![Export only the fields you need with Board Export](https://hub.adaptavist.com/hubfs/Trello/BE%20-%20fields.png)


Export in a variety of formats - Excel, CSV, PDF and image. 
![Variety of external export formats with Board Export](https://hub.adaptavist.com/hubfs/Trello/BE%20-%20formats2.png)
To view an example Trello board click [here](http://bit.ly/3psC9to). And to view the sample export files click: [CSV](https://bit.ly/3xZtsLM), [Excel](https://bit.ly/3uFdC6T), [PDF](https://bit.ly/33wmRKD), [Image](https://bit.ly/2Sz1vKs)


24/7 support team 
![A full support team to help with Board Export](https://hub.adaptavist.com/hubfs/Trello/BE%20-%20support.png)


##Use Cases
üìà  - Share a spreadsheet with clients to update them on your progress. 
‚úâÔ∏è  - Email stakeholders a weekly status report by embedding an image of your board
üóÑÔ∏è  - Maintain an archive of all your lists and cards with a PDF/Excel download
üñºÔ∏è  - Download an image/screenshot of your board to print off or showcase in a presentation

##Pricing
All users start on a 14-day free trial of the Power-up (limited to 5 cards per export) and can upgrade anytime to one of the below plans. 
**Annual billing**: $24/year ($2/month) per user for unlimited Trello boards.
OR
**Monthly billing**: $7.50/month per user for unlimited Trello boards.
(You're purchasing a license key for _one user_, not an entire board's worth of users)
NB: All cards on your board can be exported with this Power-Up, regardless of if you created/are assigned to a card.

üìπ  [Video tutorials](https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCrqmyoEdH8mMHIIpbEAxTFA)
‚ÑπÔ∏è  [Help centre](https://docs.adaptavist.com/display/_PK/BE/board-export)

listing.name: Excelefy (Export and Import cards to Excel)
listing.description:
Easily export and import your board cards to Excel Sheet.

The most comprehensive export and import tool for Trello board. Export and import the most needed information of cards to Excel sheet.

![Intro of the PowerUp](https://excelefy.d1hgvjm9dk1ut.amplifyapp.com/docs/intro.gif)

### Import the cards from Excel Sheet

Note: All the fields must be same as the export field (name, desc, url, list).

![Intro of the PowerUp](https://excelefy.d1hgvjm9dk1ut.amplifyapp.com/docs/import.gif)

### Features

- Unlimited boards
- Unlimited exports and imports
- Unlimited cards export and cards import
- Export to Excel or CSV
- Import cards to board by importing the Excel
- Export data (name, description, list, url) of cards
- 24/7 support

### Pricing

Excelefy is a free power-up.

### Privacy & Security

Your board data is safe with us. We never even see it. View our [privacy policy](https://my-main.d1hgvjm9dk1ut.amplifyapp.com/privacy) here.

### Support

We truly hope you enjoy the power-up and if you have any questions, thoughts, suggestions, we‚Äôd love to hear from you.

Visit us on our [website](https://my-main.d1hgvjm9dk1ut.amplifyapp.com) for more information.

If you need help, want to report a bug, or just want to chat about trello, send me an email at
smallpowerup@gmail.com.
listing.overview: Easily export and import your board cards to Excel Sheet.

cards.desc:
A list of the things we think we want to do, maybe not quite ready for work, but high likelihood of being worked on.

This is the staging area where specs should get fleshed out.

No limit on the list size, but we should reconsider if it gets long.
cards.name: Backlog

cards.desc:
This is a list of things that are good to pull off to work on, prioritized.

If there are too few items here, we should swarm against getting tasks ready for work.
cards.name: To Do

cards.desc:
These are the things that folks are working on.

All our engineers should have at least one item in this state.

If there are too few things here, they should be pulled off Todo.

When doing is done, cards move to Code Review.
cards.name: Doing

cards.desc:
This list is for items in code review. 

When a task has gotten approval, it moves off to Testing.

If there are too many cards here, we should break off from other tasks to get code review done.
cards.name: Code Review

cards.desc:
Cards come here after being code reviewed, and we're in a place for QA and fixing things QA finds. Design review also happens at this stage.

If we have too many cards here, we should throw a flag and figure out whether we're building things that take too many passes of QA, or if we're bottlenecked on QA time.
cards.name: Testing
